pr_body:
As discussed here: https://github.com/Diaoul/subliminal/issues/659

@Diaoul I used your suggestion: alternative_titles and alternative_series

ping @ratoaq2

//cc: @troydai, this is a pretty low risk change, I suggest we take it for the current release 

- [x] The PR has modified HISTORY.rst describing any customer-facing, functional changes. Note that this does not include changes only to help content. (see [Modifying change log](https://github.com/Azure/azure-cli/tree/master/doc/authoring_command_modules#modify-change-log)).

- [x] I adhere to the [Command Guidelines](https://github.com/Azure/azure-cli/blob/dev/doc/command_guidelines.md).

Adding benchmark result logging mechanism for RNN benchmark scripts.

Note: Some more improvements can be made to avoid separate scripts for different backends, will take up after the release.

@roywei @kalyc

Fixes #2708 

Using typical values of  `dimensions` and `rangeND` this optimization produces around a 5.3x speedup for the affected lines in _getNeighborsND. When profiling code that used _getNeighborsND, this line contributed 68% of total runtime, making this optimization very significant for such code. This change passes all unit and integration test.

@scottpurdy @vitaly-krugl

Required for capnp files to be included in eggs.

fixes #2259 

@rhyolight please review
@jcasner @unixorn  fyi

Example: `http://localhost:8080/alerts?api-key=demo-key&limit=50&page=1&service=foo`

```
{
  status: "ok",
  total: 1,
  pageSize: 50,
  statusCounts: {
    closed: 1
  },
  alerts: [ ... ],
  page: 1,
  more: false,
  severityCounts: {
    normal: 1
  },
  lastTime: "2014-12-21T11:49:52.024Z",
  pages: 1,
  autoRefresh: true
}
```

- Move ``ftw.referencewidget`` dependency to ``contenttypes`` extras, since it is only used for the content types subpackage.

- Remove ``plone.formwidget.contenttree`` dependency, as it is not used at all because it was replaced with ``ftw.referencewidget``.

// cc @tschanzt

This should fix #342 and #343.
y-axis inversion is now done with a function, that first checks if it was inverted already. Legends are now not plotted by default.

@tacaswell, I just realized this crosses your older PR #178. Maybe we can work out a combination of both, yours has to be rebased anyway. There has to be some more cleaning in `plots.py`.
